# Analysis of üí¨-discussion Discord Channel

## 1. Summary
The discussion primarily revolves around token migration issues from AI16Z to ElizaOS. A major controversy involves Bithumb exchange, which allowed trading after the November 11th snapshot date, creating problems for users who traded after this date. The exchange initially announced support for the swap but later reversed its decision, claiming late notification from the ElizaOS team. Users are frustrated about who bears responsibility for tokens traded after the snapshot date.

The team is handling migration tickets manually for users who held tokens before the snapshot. Several users expressed concerns about the project's direction and exchange listings. There were mentions of Babylon.market as a joint venture with Ethereum developers for agent infrastructure, training, and benchmarking. The team participated in a MEXC spaces event and a discussion with the MOCA team. Some users reported potential scams related to migration attempts.

## 2. FAQ
Q: What about ai16z that was traded on exchanges after the 11th? (asked by degenwtf) A: Centralized exchanges operate differently, and the team is only swapping up to the snapshot amount, which creates complications for exchanges that allowed trading after the snapshot. (answered by dracok)
Q: Why is ElizaOS not listed in the x402 Ecosystem in coin gecko? (asked by Jo) A: Good question. (answered by Odilitime)
Q: In that case, is it possible to convert to elizaos tokens on the swap site if I hold ai16z in my personal wallet and bought before November? (asked by KARA) A: Should be possible. (answered by Odilitime)
Q: Are there no bribes for elizaos on aerodrome? (asked by vebevebe) A: Unanswered
Q: Why is the exchange only in stock now, and there is no contract? (asked by SKW) A: Contact your exchange and ask them. (answered by Odilitime)
Q: How can I proof november 11th snap shot? (asked by Í±∞Î∂ÅÏïå) A: Ideally bithumb would help you out here. (answered by Kenk)
Q: Is there a recording of shaws speech at devconnect? (asked by Arceon) A: Unanswered
Q: It was announced a few months ago that the ElizaOS token would be listed on t1 exchanges. Are there any developments in this regard? (asked by Numerical Methods) A: Unanswered
Q: How quickly will support review my ticket? (asked by Garaj) A: We'll get there asap. (answered by Kenk)
Q: Has the discussion between the team and Bithumb ended, or are there still matters under negotiation? (asked by good) A: Unanswered
